postcontent:
Buy now and save $$$ with no wait period to be custom made with armor pockets!

Size 54 Long. I'm 6'2 250 and this fits perfect. Leather runs a bit tighter than other jackets.  
Made in USA!

This has the hard to get special order hidden internal armor pockets for the spine, shoulders, and elbows. This jacket has an extremely warm liner with a hidden fleece neck wrap, and zippered vents all over that can be opened. This is the only high quality original old school style jacket with hidden armor pockets. This is truly a top of the line USA made jacket. Fox Creek leather is hand made in america with a lifetime guarantee. This is the best protective jacket in the market. It vents in the warm weather, keeps wind off in the winter, and will protect from injury. This is a very heavy substantial jacket.

Bought this and now have to sell my bike. My loss is your gain! Wore this jacket less than an hour and it was amazing in the cold weather. Totally blocks the wind and the removable liner keeps the warmth in. 

From Fox Creek:
Crafted from 1.4-1.6mm naked leather.
Dual front, rear, and sleeve vents for maximum airflow.
Adjustable half belt and laced sides deliver an optimal fit for all seasons.
Armor provisional pockets in the elbows, shoulders and back of most sizes* (armor not included)
Two inside pockets: Left with a snap closure, Right with a zipper closure.
Removable insulated full sleeve liner with hide-away fleece neck warmer.
Padded and extended kidney panel.
Antique Brass YKK Hardware


Men's Classic Motorcycle Jackets are the most emotionally volatile and historically rich leather jackets we have. When I put one on I can't decide if I am going to ride a motorcycle, vandalize a town or give someone a ticket. Like any piece of great art it means different things to different people.
In 1953 at the age of seven, inspired by Marlon Brando in "The Wild One", I asked my parents if I could get a Men's Classic Motorcycle Jacket I. I did not understand the social implications of this leather motorcycle jacket. My mother looked at me like I had asked her if I could cannibalize my infant brother. She began to cry softly, ashamed that I was drawn to such evil.
I went on to become a small time juvenile delinquent and performed many reprehensible acts but none of them elicited the reaction this simple request did.
In addition to parental alienation, the leather jacket is well suited for motorcycle riding. It's cut extra long in the back with a padded kidney panel. Dual front and rear vents move the air easily through a mesh shell while an internal wind flap stops it cold at the zipper. A zip out full sleeve insulated liner completes the climate control package.
Side lacing enables you to contour the motorcycle jacket to your body and an inside snap pocket is set in the leather facing where it won't rip out. Leather is 1.4 to 1.6 mm soft, thick and supple with a dull luster.
The difference between the Men's Classic Motorcycle Jacket I and Men's Classic Motorcycle Jacket II is that the Men's Classic Motorcycle Jacket I has a watch pocket and breast pocket on the left side and a half belt in front. Outside of that they are the same leather jacket.
Please read How Your Motorcycle Jacket Is Supposed To Fit if you have any questions on sizing.
Here you can find pictures of Joe Yarzebinski's Men's Classic Motorcycle Jacket I that went down after sliding on loose gravel.
Check out the reviews of the Men's Classic Motorcycle Jacket I at vTwinBiker.com,WestCoastBikers.com, and ChoppersRule.com. You can read more third party reviews of Fox Creek Leather motorcycle jackets and other products here.

The new polymer 80% lower receiver for your AR15 platform is engineered and manufactured by James Madison Tactical (JMT) in the USA.  This is not your average polymer 80 lower, in fact, The JMT polymer 80 is fully engineered using current finite element structural analysis for reliable, long-term high performance.

POLYMER 80 versus ALUMINUM
After much research in polymer 80 AR15 lowers, JMT has created its own formula of hybrid polymers and fibers with additional reinforcements in high stress areas to bring you the best AR15 lower on the market today.  All of the JMT polymer 80 lowers are engineered to Mil Spec tolerances and because it is fashioned from extremely durable fiber polymer materials there are no concerns about corrosion as you may find in aluminum AR15 lowers.

IN FIELD DURABILITY
JMT uses only the best high quality hybrid fiber/polymer materials, advanced engineering, precision manufacturing and stringent quality controls.  This way you can trust it not only in the harshest field environments but for personal protection as well.

PARTS INTERCHANGEABILITY
The Polymer 80 AR15 80% lower is designed specifically to Mil Spec tolerances for a high level of interchangeability with other Mil Spec AR15 parts and accessories on the market today.  This is achieved through current technology and computer aided manufacturing processes combined with exacting quality control procedures.

PERSONAL DEFENSE AND PROTECTION
How you decide to defend and protect yourself and your family is a personal matter.  No one wishes to experience a personal breach of your safety or a home invasion but it does happen.  The mission at JMT is to give you the assurance in a product you can trust.

The operations left to be completed to complete your Polymer 80 AR15 80% lower are as follows: fire control group, trigger pin, hammer pin, trigger slot and the safety selector hole. This is a not an FFL item. This is not a complete receiver and still requires machining to be done.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Savage Model 10 FCPXP Long Range Sniper, 308, Bushnell Tactical Elite Scope
postcontent:
Sorry for the long post, but if you're serious about a long range gun you will read it.  All items on this gun are brand new within the last 3 months.  I put this gun together thinking I would get into long range shooting.  It hasn't worked out.

Gun: Savage Model 10, FCPXP, 308 Winchester,  heavy bull barrel, accutrigger, detachable box mag, comes with single shot adapter for the range, less than 100 rds fired, shoots .5 MOA at 100 yrds- excellent condition

Accessories: 
Choate tactical aluminum bedded stock with large palm swell
EGW one piece picatinny rail
Burris Xtreme 30 mm rings-low
Butler Creek lens caps
Bipod- only item that is not new- but in good condition

Scope: this is the crown jewel of this set up
Bushnell Elite Tactical 6-24x50 illuminated reticle- Amazing
Mildot reticle
FRONT FOCAL PLANE- please do your research- this is the most important thing about this scope- a front focal objective means that the reticle grows with the magnification therefore the mil calculations remain the same no matter what magnification setting you are in- most scopes, even some of the expensive Leupolds don't have this feature.  It spares you from having to be a math genius at the range.  It also allows you to range your target with the reticle.  An amazing feature
Large military style target turrets- .1 Mil per click- this means that the mildot reticle and the mil adjustment turrets match- most mildot reticle scopes have MOA adjustments, which means you have to be a math genius again and have a whole other set of numbers at different magnification levels- this scope takes the difficulty out of long range shooting
30 mm main tube
Perfect Tracking- you can adjust the windage and elevation up to 1000 yards then return it to zero and it will be spot on
Do your homework on this scope- watch the youtube videos 
Costs $1000
This scope is new- unlike the Bushnell models of a couple years ago, this scope has enough elevation built into it to shoot 1000 yards without a MOA rail
This gun is ready to shoot 1000+ yards right now


I have over $2000 invested into this set up.  I will sell for $1500 bc I need the cash.  You could never build this gun for that money.
I will sell the scope separately, its new with the box, for $800
- I will include over 100 rds of match quality ammo in a MTM ammo dry case if you buy the whole set up

The DB380 differs from most small modern pocket autos. Most have a hammer action, but the DB380 is striker-fired. Originally designed for the American market, the USP (Universal Self-loading Pistol) has found international acceptance as an accurate and ultra-reliable handgun. Features favored by U.S. law enforcement and military users provided much of the design criteria for the USP. The controls are uniquely American, influenced by such famous designs as the Government Model 1911 pistol.

All USPs use a fiber-reinforced polymer frame stiffened by stainless steel inserts at areas subject to stress and friction. HK pioneered this use of polymer materials in the production of handguns more than 30 years ago with the development of the VP70Z and P9S pistols.

The USP control lever, a combination safety and decocking lever, is frame mounted and quickly accessible, unlike the slide-mounted safeties common on many semi-automatic pistols.

Using a modified Browning-type action with a special patented recoil reduction system, the USP recoil reduction system reduces recoil effects on pistol components and also lowers the recoil forces felt by the shooter. This same recoil reduction system has been tested and proven in the HK Mark 23 pistol developed for the U.S. Special Operations Command. The USP recoil reduction system is insensitive to ammunition types and requires no special adjustment or maintenance. It functions effectively in all USP models.

The modular design of the USP's internal components allows the control lever function to be switched from the left to the right side of the pistol for left-handed shooters. The USP can also be converted from one type of trigger firing mode to another. This includes combination double-action and single-action (DA/SA) modes and double action only (DAO) modes.
